LGPL-2.1 imposes restrictions on static linking that are more stringent
than the MIT license used by libpromeki.  Specifically, LGPL Section 6
requires that when a "work that uses the Library" is distributed with
the Library statically linked in, the distributor must provide the means
for users to re-link the work against a modified version of the Library
(e.g. by providing object files or by using dynamic linking).

As of this writing, the static linking of libsndfile into
libpromeki-proav is a known compliance issue under active investigation.
The library is used for its broadcast WAV (BWF) file support, which is
a requirement for professional audio workflows.  Options being evaluated
include:

  1. Switching libsndfile to dynamic linking (the simplest LGPL-
     compliant approach, but adds a runtime dependency for consumers).

  2. Replacing libsndfile with a permissively-licensed alternative
     that supports the required broadcast WAV features.

  3. Providing object files alongside the shared library to satisfy
     LGPL Section 6(a) re-linking requirements.

Until this is resolved, users who redistribute libpromeki binaries
should be aware of the LGPL obligations.  The full text of the LGPL-2.1
is available in the source tree at thirdparty/libsndfile/COPYING.


